ygData.messageBody:
Now that I'm ready for it I feel good about it - stinks for newbies though -
I did discover that place early in life and it was incredible - never more
than 10 people in the entire dungeon.

South Ro does have Terronantula - that makes it interesting enough :)

-----Original Message-----
From: John Carney [mailto:jcarney@...]
Sent: Wednesday, December 08, 1999 5:37 PM
To: EQ-Monks@onelist.com
Subject: RE: [EQ-Monks] General grousing


From: "John Carney" <jcarney@...>

>South Ro is great - not crowded, many camps, etc. etc.

Aye, South Ro is AWESOME. Of course, by the time I noticed that, damn near
everything was green to me.... I wouldn't be surprised to see South Ro take
a similar path to Split Paw (if that EVER gets done).

Out of Curiousity, is anyone else besides me greatly looking forward to
SplitPaw being changed?

Stone
